7	-- Entity:					TODO
8	--
9	-- Description:
10	-- -------------------------------------
11	-- Computes from an input word, a word of the same size that has, at most,
12	-- one bit set. The output contains a set bit at the position of the rightmost
13	-- set bit of the input if and only if such a set bit exists in the input.
14	--
15	-- A typical use case for this computation would be an arbitration over
16	-- requests with a fixed and strictly ordered priority. The terminology of
17	-- the interface assumes this use case and provides some useful extras:
18	--
19	-- * Set tin <= '0' (no input token) to disallow grants altogether.
20	-- * Read tout (unused token) to see whether or any grant was issued.
21	-- * Read bin to obtain the binary index of the rightmost detected one bit.
22	--   The index starts at zero (0) in the rightmost bit position.
23	--
24	-- This implementation uses carry chains for wider implementations.
